<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-229-394  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 229 394.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Network World  March 12 1990 v7 n11 p4(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Coalition fights proposed bill to lift RBHC restraints; bill wouldlet RBHCs compete in banned markets. (regional Bell holdingcompanies)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Brown, Bob.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Telecommunication vendors and users met in Washington D.C.andP;  toprotest the House Subcommittee on Telecommunications and Finance's'Telecommunications Policy Act of 1990,' a draft bill proposed toeliminate business restrictions imposed on the regional Bellholding companies.andP;  The draft bill is designed to allow theregional Bell companies to compete in some areas in equipmentmanufacturing, information services and long-distance markets.andP;  Italso recommends that the Federal Communications Commission, ratherthan the courts, oversees the changes.andP;  The coalition of users andvendors argued that the bill would result in fewer choices andhigher prices in equipment and network services.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Bell Regional Holding CompaniesDeregulationTelecommunicationsUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionGovernment RegulationManufacturingInformation ServicesCommunications Service SuppliersLegislation.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>